It requires a high level of organizational, technical and financial efforts.
Creating and developing a sustainable European transport infrastructure often requires difficult compromises with European and national policy objectives, such as environmental preservation.
Precisely because of the required environmental protection measures, the construction of the transport infrastructure is expensive.
When planning and allocating the construction of transport routes, administrations can save considerable financial resources and use them for other useful purposes through careful action and decision-making.
